Notes from my debugging:
 - Chrome iOS (CriOS) does not support opening ObjectUrls. It gives empty page.
 - This was already discussed on [Google Forums](https://groups.google.com/a/chromium.org/forum/#!topic/chromium-html5/RKQ0ZJIj7c4) without success, just workaround
 - Workaround was published on [Stack Overlow](http://stackoverflow.com/questions/24485077/how-to-open-blob-url-on-chrome-ios). Here is slightly modified version that worked for me. It uses datalinks.

```javascript
var reader = new FileReader();
var blob = new Blob(['Hello world'], {type: 'plain/text'});
reader.onload = function(e){
  var bdata = btoa(reader.result);
  window.location.href = 'data:' + blob.type + ';base64,' + bdata;
}
reader.readAsDataURL(blob);
```

 - It is still a workaround, Chrome iOS does not download the file. It opens it in the tab.
 - `data:attachment/file` did not work for me. CriOS shown file for download, but with download error. After pressing download again button, error again.
 - `data:application/octet-stream` worked even if real type was `image/png`, image was still shown.
 - This workaround may have problems with big files. Even files slightly over 1MB take some time to load in the tab.
 - I've submitted a pull request #240

