I checked the assembly and without declaring `get_norm` and `normalize` like you did with `dot3` and `dot`, g++ won't use it. The float implementation of `two_means` forced the usage of the float variants and thus created the speedup. My optimized `two_means` is mostly unreadable and does not affect performance at all.
