What's happening here:

Start:

```
server {
  listen 8000;
}
server {
  listen 80;
}
```
both with `server_name` set correctly.

Then we install the cert to the first one:
```
server {
  listen 8000;
  listen 443;
  ssl_certificate...
}
server {
  listen 80;
}
```
Then we put the redirect in the other one:
```
server {
  listen 8000;
  listen 443;
  ssl_certificate...
}
server {
  if ($host = ...)
  listen 80;
}
```

Then, Certbot is run again.
This time, we install the cert in the second one:
```
server {
  listen 8000;
  listen 443 ssl;
  ssl_certificate...
}
server {
  if ($host = ...)
  listen 80;
  listen 443 ssl;
  ssl_certificate...
}
```
Then, we're asked to enable redirect, so we split the latter server block in 2:
```
server {
  listen 8000;
  listen 443 ssl;
  ssl_certificate...
}
server {
  if ($host = ...) [redirect 1]
  listen 443 ssl;
  ssl_certificate...
}
server {
  if ($host = ...) [redirect 2]
  listen 80;
  return 404;
}
```
But we put redirect 1 in there last run, so we don't know to remove it.

So the question is, why did we put `listen 443 ssl` in the `listen 8000` server in the first place? If we stop doing that, that should fix this problem.

