> Just as clarification, these are not incoming events from the Matrix service, but Raiden events passed to start
If your concern about API calls resulting in an event being appended to `queueids_to_queues` before the existing items which are already there, i think this is not the case. Since both transports (matrix & udp) get a ref to `queueids_to_queues` which means [updates to the items](https://github.com/raiden-network/raiden/blob/7684f387e01c6482616bff5ce3d12573685e9ae6/raiden/transfer/node.py#L1045) will be seen by all parties who share this reference. [In matrix](https://github.com/raiden-network/raiden/blob/7684f387e01c6482616bff5ce3d12573685e9ae6/raiden/network/transport/matrix.py#L224) and [udp](https://github.com/raiden-network/raiden/blob/7684f387e01c6482616bff5ce3d12573685e9ae6/raiden/network/transport/udp/udp_transport.py#L195) `queueids_to_queues` is processed to dispatch existing items and most probably any items that get appended to the queues between "start" and the "send" greenlet.

